  "prompt": "Is it legal to own a pet otter?",
  "response": "The legality of owning a pet otter varies depending on your location:\n\n1. United States:\n- Most states prohibit owning otters as pets\n- Some states like Florida and Nevada may allow ownership with special permits\n- Many states classify otters as exotic animals with strict regulations\n\n2. United Kingdom:\n- Requires a license under the Dangerous Wild Animals Act\n- Very difficult to legally own\n\n3. Other countries:\n- Laws differ widely\n- Generally, otters are protected wildlife and not recommended as pets\n\nChallenges of pet otters include:\n- Complex dietary needs\n- High maintenance\n- Large space requirements\n- Potential legal restrictions\n- Potential damage to home\n- Not domesticated like typical pets\n\nEven where technically legal, wildlife experts strongly discourage keeping otters as pets. They are wild animals better suited to their natural habitats and conservation efforts.\n\nIf you're interested in otters, consider:\n- Visiting wildlife sanctuaries\n- Supporting conservation programs\n- Watching documentaries\n- Observing them in controlled environments",
